Version (0.90):
Released 2001.09.26

	- Windows support added! The Cog Development Application now runs 
	  correctly and completely under Microsoft Windows. The only 
	  requirement is that Python is installed.

	- Gnome support removed from Glade, and all widgets recreated 
	  to use GTK+ only. Currently, on the GTK+ libraries are supported 
	  on Windows, and incorporating the Gnome libraries was just using 
	  unecessary memory. This was necessary to run the program under 
	  Windows.

	- All Glade windows rewritten to use a dynamic layout, instead of
	  a fixed layout. Besides a cleaner, more consistent look, this 
	  also means that different fonts can be used without labels being
	  obscured (this was an issue under Windows).

	- Debug Mode added. Debugging messages are never printed to stdout 
	  when Debug Mode is enabled.

	- "Image Directory" entry added. This makes it easier to use 
	  the same game data with different graphics files. For instance, 
	  if you have a high and a low resolution version of the same 
	  game, you only have to change this entry to point to another 
	  directory, and the rest of the game data remains intact.

	- After adding the Image Directory option, an incompatibility was
	   made between this release and earlier game files. A conversion
	   script was included to transition old game files to the new format.

	- About box rewritten, since this was previously a Gnome
	  Component.

	- General code cleanup; many unecessary comments were removed.


Version (0.82):
Released 2001.06.19

	- Event builder and editor have been updated to include object
	  numbers as well as names in their listings. The CogScript API
	  has been updated to reflect this change.

	- New directions are selected by default after being added to a 
	  room in the room editor

	- Added direction description handler to room editor

	- Fixed a bug in the code to add a new obstruction

	- Fixed a bug in the event editor that caused events to be dropped

	- If you enter a filename for loading on the command line, the
	  same file name will be used by default when saving

	- Fixed bugs in both item and obstruction editors which caused 
	  blank graphics to overwrite room's graphic when examining
	  objects

	- Fixed a typo in the room editor that caused problems when adding 
	  a new room and clearing the current room

	- Fixed a bug with the inventory lister in the player editor


Version (0.81):
Released 2001.06.14

	- Fixed blank-string bug with Obstructions in Room Editor
	  and in CogObjects.py (blank strings should have been set to
	  Null), which was causing the Cog Engine to fail to load

	- Fixed blank-string bug with Items in Room Editor and in
	  CogObjects.py (blank strings should have been set to Null) which
	  was causing the Item indicator to indicate items in all rooms,
	  including empty ones

	- Player Current Room selection improved to use a Combo Box, and
	  jython scripts have been updated to convert changes properly

	- Player Editor Inventory display improved to work same way as 
	  Item selection in Room Editor

	- Room Editor now permits "Has Visited" status to be modified,
	  and jython scripts have been updated to convert changes properly

	- Player Inventory should be list, not tuple - CogObjects.py fixed

	- Fixed export_cog_data.py bug that failed to set Player's
	  Inventory Array to correct size - prevented "get
	  object" commands to function correctly


